---
import ArticleLayout from '../../../layouts/ArticleLayout.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: "why-switch", label: "Why Contractors Switch" },
  { id: "fit-score", label: "Alternative Fit Score" },
  { id: "miss-vs-save", label: "What You'll Miss vs Save" },
  { id: "workiz", label: "1. Workiz" },
  { id: "jobber", label: "2. Jobber" },
  { id: "fieldedge", label: "3. FieldEdge" },
  { id: "service-fusion", label: "4. Service Fusion" },
  { id: "faq", label: "FAQ" },
  { id: "verdict", label: "Verdict" }
];
const faqItems = [
  { q: "Is it hard to switch from ServiceTitan?", a: "The technical migration (exporting data, importing to a new tool) takes 1-3 weeks depending on the platform. The harder part is retraining your team. Budget 2-4 weeks for the full transition. Most alternatives offer migration support." },
  { q: "Will I lose my customer data?", a: "No. ServiceTitan allows data export. All alternatives accept CSV imports. Your customer records, job history, and contact information can be transferred." },
  { q: "What features will I actually miss?", a: "The two features most contractors miss are ServiceTitan's marketing attribution dashboard and its pricebook with dynamic pricing. If these are critical to your operation, switching may not be worth the savings." },
  { q: "Can I try an alternative before canceling ServiceTitan?", a: "Yes. Jobber and Workiz both offer free trials. Run them in parallel for 2 weeks before making the switch." },
  { q: "What about my ServiceTitan contract?", a: "ServiceTitan uses annual contracts. Check your renewal date and cancellation terms. Some contractors negotiate early termination by citing the cost savings." }
];
---

<ArticleLayout
  title="5 ServiceTitan Alternatives for HVAC Companies (2026) — HVAC Software Hub"
  description="Paying too much for ServiceTitan? We scored 5 alternatives on cost savings, feature parity, and switching ease."
  canonicalPath="/hvac/crm/servicetitan-alternatives"
  category="CRM & Automation"
  publishDate="2026-02-17"
  readTime="12 min read"
  intent="BOFU"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  faqItems={faqItems}
>
<div class="container py-8">
        <div class="flex gap-12">
          <article class="flex-1 min-w-0 max-w-3xl">

            <div class="prose mt-8" id="why-switch">
              <h2>Why HVAC Contractors Look for ServiceTitan Alternatives</h2>
              <p>
                ServiceTitan is the most powerful field service management platform available. But power comes at a cost — literally. At <strong>$245-$398 per technician per month</strong>, plus implementation fees of $5,000-$50,000, many HVAC companies find themselves paying for features they do not use. Reddit threads from HVAC owners consistently cite three reasons for switching: cost, contract lock-in, and complexity.
              </p>
              <p>
                This guide scores five alternatives on the factors that matter most to a ServiceTitan switcher: <strong>how much you will save, how many features you will keep, and how hard it is to switch</strong>.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div id="fit-score" class="mt-10">
