<!-- FAQ Section -->
<div id="faq" class="mt-10">
  <h2 class="font-semibold text-2xl mb-4" style="font-family: var(--font-heading);">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <div class="space-y-0">
    <div class="faq-item">
      <p class="faq-question">Is it hard to switch from ServiceTitan?</p>
      <p class="faq-answer">The technical migration (exporting data, importing to a new tool) takes 1-3 weeks depending on the platform. The harder part is retraining your team. Budget 2-4 weeks for the full transition. Most alternatives offer migration support.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <p class="faq-question">Will I lose my customer data?</p>
      <p class="faq-answer">No. ServiceTitan allows data export. All alternatives accept CSV imports. Your customer records, job history, and contact information can be transferred.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <p class="faq-question">What features will I actually miss?</p>
      <p class="faq-answer">The two features most contractors miss are ServiceTitan's marketing attribution dashboard and its pricebook with dynamic pricing. If these are critical to your operation, switching may not be worth the savings.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <p class="faq-question">Can I try an alternative before canceling ServiceTitan?</p>
      <p class="faq-answer">Yes. Jobber and Workiz both offer free trials. Run them in parallel for 2 weeks before making the switch.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <p class="faq-question">What about my ServiceTitan contract?</p>
      <p class="faq-answer">ServiceTitan uses annual contracts. Check your renewal date and cancellation terms. Some contractors negotiate early termination by citing the cost savings.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
